race.comment: STAR RAPPER (2) had been in sound form but last start he was safely held when 12th over 1000m at Pakenham. Rhys McLeod has been in the money at every start aboard this five-year-old gelding so a better run is on the cards. MERE MORSEL (3) showed the benefit of earlier racing with an improved run last start and there's no reason he can't go on with it here. THE NARRATOR (4) didn't do a bad job to finish 1.3 lengths away in sixth last start over 1200m at Warrnambool. That followed a win on debut at Benalla. Ideally placed and is sure to bounce back to form. YOURAWAY (10) got back on top of the ground last start with a good win at Mortlake and his Soft track stats read well for this. Easy to make a case for him.
